nodes.body:
Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/0bc05655-2638-4e6d-b6b2-82ef905e8d18) for commit 8fe3b6ac8b6ef7a3b6d4353a8cf48fcc7f928a66.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/d9ef4bb0-357b-48b0-b289-ff405ab6782e/to/0bc05655-2638-4e6d-b6b2-82ef905e8d18) against commit a93cf1574b04b6aca9fd392ca6b1aaebe4ea2e7d:
```diff
  Benchmark                                                         Metric           Change
  =========================================================================================
- build                                                             interpretation    12.6%
+ ~Mathlib.Analysis.NormedSpace.PiTensorProduct.InjectiveSeminorm   instructions      -3.9%
```

As discussed with @adomani via DM, the easiest way forward to land this PR is to
- land #12339 (as this PR extends its logic - so it's easier to review and agree on the core logic first)
- review the linter itself (not enabling it in mathlib yet)
- automatically fix mathlib, by writing a short `refactor` programme

Marking as blocked on the first PR. Review of that is helpful and certainly welcome!
